I realize that this may be a topic for another group being that this
is about a common law relationship but I thought here would be a good
place to start.

I'm 41 and have been with my fiance for almost 5 years. He and I were
highschool sweethearts and we both went on to marry others only to
have both marriages tank at roughly the same time.

I was adamant that I would not consider dating until after his wife
had agreed to separate and eventually divorce, and move out of the
&quot;marital&quot; home. She did in late 2001, and in early 2002 we started
dating again. In December 2002 I moved in with him.

We discussed marriage, and we agreed that it was a bit of a sore topic
for both of us, especially him. I did not bring it up again until he
proposed in March of 2004. We bought my engagement ring and wedding
ring in July of the same year, and had hoped to marry in April of
2005. We even bought gifts for the best man and maid of honour.

As he is self employed, and cash flow being erratic, it did not
happen. Nor did it happen later. The marriage license application, the
final page of both our divorce decrees (originals as the application
must be accompanied with the document showing the court seal), and a
copy of my birth certificate have all disappeared.

For the most part our relationship has been steady sailing, with few
arguments. However, he blew up on Sunday because of a number of things
he had chosen not to discuss with me prior. The trigger was that he
wanted to go out, but neglected to tell me he wanted to ride our
motorcycles. This being especially important because of his 8 1/2 year
old son, whose riding gear was not in our home, but at his mother's. I
offered to let the boy use my helmet, and being the typical mom (I
have a 15 year old son of my own who was at a friend's), I volunteered
to stay home so the child could go out with his dad.

I have now come to the irrfutable conclusion that, after nearly 5
years together, numerous postponements of a wedding, no further
discussion of setting a date to even go to city hall, and no other
legal assurances (ie a will) in my favour that he has never had any
intention of marrying. With no will and no legal marriage, should
anything happen to him I am in legal limbo. Our rented house is owned
by his sister, and all I have is the clothes on my back and no
furniture.

I am despondent. I want to scream at him that despite that he says he
wants me enough to live with him, to sleep with him and care for him,
his son and his home, he does not want me enough to marry me. He has
always found a way to pay the bills and to get the nifty accessories
for his motorcycle (fairing, trunk, CB radio). It tears me apart to
realize that he just doesn't care enough to make things happen for a
wedding. Even a small one in our home, with an officiant attending at
the house than a big affair in our church. If he cared half as much
for me, and wanted me half as much as his toys, he'd have made it
legal long ago.

I can't even stand to look at him any more.

S
