It's odd to me that in the next to last paragraph, you say you want to marry
him, then you say you can't stand to look at him.  I think you're very upset
and are connecting too much of your upset to the marriage issue.

If I were he, I'd have no idea it was so important to you - the marriage
part.  The legal part is something that middle aged people start thinking
about
(death and property, etc.) but he may not be thinking about it as much as
you
are.  You are close to sounding morbid about your reasons for wanting to get
married.

Maybe back up a little?  You started out sounding like the two of you
really care about each other.  If you're paying more than your share of the
bills (he doesn't pay for his own motorcycle goodies?) that's a separate
issue,
and wouldn't be resolved by getting married or not, I don't think.

If you just started disliking him this weekend, I'd wait till my mood had
settled
down and start planning a simple wedding.  Any reason he wouldn't go along
with it?

A.

